snippet.title: What Makes Cheap Drums Cheap (And Good Drums Good)??
snippet.description:
What, really, is the difference between cheap drums and good drums?  How significant are the differences and how do they affect the behavior of the drum?  And what can be done to improve the quality of truly cheap drums?  

No, I don't recommend buying uber cheap drums and then trying to fix them up (big hassle and probably as much expense as just buying a better drum to begin with), but for the sake of demonstration in this video I do improve the craftsmanship of an otherwise cheap snare drum (with cheap hardware) just to see what role craftsmanship plays in the manufacture of good drums.  So let's get into it!!  It's the most fun you'll have all week, of course!

Jon Zoog (Dallas Drum) can be reached at https://dallasdrum.com 
I have no financial affiliation with Dallas Drum or Jon Zoog -- he just knows his stuff (and is a really cool dude to boot!!)

snippet.title: Why Do We Love The Acrolite Anyway? --  Deep Dive Into The World's Most Famous 'Student' Snare Drum!
snippet.description:
In 1963 Ludwig introduced their now legendary Acrolite model snare drum made of their new 'wonder metal!'  Its development took place during the time that  Ludwig was trying to reduce manufacturing costs for their flagship "Super Ludwig" model snare drum.  The solution to their flagship problem also enabled them to make a high-quality, cost effective metal snare for the student market.  

Let's unpack some drum history together!  It's the most fun you'll have all week! ;)


Videos I mentioned in this one:

My Black Beauty snare that burned up in a fire: https://youtu.be/7vP6xjge4iQ

Super Ludwig vs. Supra-Phonic Comparison:  https://youtu.be/RRtd6VRw5io

Ultimate Acrolite Comparison (5 drums!): https://youtu.be/SUl9IV3EPQ4

The Impact of Mass on a Drum's Sound:  https://youtu.be/sKDRDRAphy8

snippet.title: Does it matter REALLY what wood(s) your drums are made of?  Part Five in series on drum physics!
snippet.description:
I've been often asked to speak about the effect of wood selection on drum shell construction.  Since I don't generally do things halfway this is another long one, one I hope will be worth it for those with a desire to truly unpack the subject.  

What else can I say? It's the most fun you'll have all week!!!  ;). Come join me!

2:52 So what the differences?  Appearance...
3:58 Affect of wood on sound (i.e.acoustic guitars)
5:33 Does type of wood affect drums similarly?
7:11 Areas of impact on the performance of drums
7:43 Relevant properties of wood
9:32 The Gold Standard - Sugar Maple

snippet.title: That's Not What I've Been Told!  Drum Sound Physics, Part ONE
snippet.description:
In this first of a series of geeky videos devoted to demystifying various factors that contribute to a drum's sound I refer to the document that first got my brain cells cranking on the subject almost 40 years ago (dang, I'm old!).  Over the last few decades I have found the physics contained therein to be absolutely true (though much of today's drum marketing and design objectives would appear to dispute it).  

This is gonna be fun, I promise.  Come join me!!

0:00 Intro
2:44 'Research'
4:51 The Drum Head
5:51 The Drum Shell
7:45 'Must Not Vibrate'
10:10 Flectional Resistance
10:42 Mass
12:26 Frictional Loss
12:58 Bearing Edge
13:06 Shell Wall Thickness
14:04 Fundamental Note Muffled
15:38 Thick Shell Has Same Overtone Spectrum As Thin Shell
16:52 My Reason For Making This Video
19:25 My Wish (Hello, Drum Manufacturers?)
19:37 Why Does Any Of This Matter?
20:09 What Do People Mean By "Resonance?"
21:40 If You Really Want Sustain...
23:34 Wrap Up
24:18 "But Joel, Thin Shells Resonate!!"
25:59 Teaser.... :)

snippet.title: The Ultimate Bearing Edge Test!
snippet.description:
Check out our latest episode on bearing edges.
We tried to demystify the topic of bearing edges by testing four different edges scientifically.

You will be able to hear what the different types of bearing edges sound like and also get some impressions of experts on the topic.
It will make it a lot easier for you to be able to choose the right type of bearing edge for your drumkit.

snippet.title: Bearing Edges -- Drum Sound Physics Part II
snippet.description:
In the second installment of this series on drum sound physics I discuss bearing edges and their affect on a drum's performance.  Let's see if I can't distill this topic down to the important bits.  Come join me!!

0:00 Introduction
2:11 Bearing edge definition and purpose
6:55 Keeping it simple -- two basic types of edges
9:50 Sharp edges
12:24 Round edges
17:10 Roundover edges
20:43 Single cut edges
21:41 Dual/counter cuts
22:13 Effect of edge angle on 'event horizon'
27:05 Effect of edge angle on drum shell mass
28:53 Conclusion

snippet.title: Drum Restoration, 26" bass drum. John Bonham Green Sparkle Ludwig Drum Set Build PT. 1
snippet.description:
This is the start of finally building my John Bonham replica green sparkle set, it's taken me years to track down the drums, parts and pieces (mainly the 26" bass drum) but also good candidates for a rewrap, all of these drums had wrap issues, i do not rewrap nice original drums as people need those to complete other sets. This set is for me and will stay in my collection, as a huge Bonham fan this is something I've wanted to do for a very long time. 

This is just how i do things, not really a "how to" video. As with everything I'm still always learning, figuring things out myself and adapting my years of wood wooding experience to repairing drums. I learn something new with every repair and each has it's own challenges, from simple to extensive like this. i had thought about replacing the whole diamond shaped area in blue tape of the inner ply but i think this worked out pretty well, it's not absolutely perfect which rarely exists in the vintage drum realm anyways lol but in the end it's strong, looks decent and no one will ever see it with the coated heads on anyways. almost every replica kit i've seen has a similar repair done as these 14 x 26 3 ply bass drums do not pop up every day, actually very rarely, virgin undrilled even less or never lol and usually very expensive so there is not a lot to chose from. 

i was extremely happy to come across this one, i didn't notice the hackery of the tom mount at first as it was covered by a gasket and washers but for what i paid for it and just even getting a chance to own one i'm still vary happy with the purchase.

as always, thanks for watching.

#drums #vintagedrums #ludwig #ludwigdrums #vintage #JohnBonham #LedZepplin #drummer

snippet.title: How to stain and clear coat a drum set
snippet.description:
In this video I show how to sand, clean, stain, and clear coat a drum set. I wanted to restore this Pearl Export drum set to have more of a wood grain finish.

I left on the old heads and used stain polyurethane and brasso to accomplish this. I also had several grits of sandpaper.

snippet.title: 'Clean & Restore' my old love and hate 'Rick Owens' suede high sneakers - VETIVER
snippet.description:
Hello, today I prepared a special asmr video. 
I had a pair of Rick Owens high-top sneakers that were too worn out to throw away,
 so I decided to restore them with a 3d printer. 
These shoes were one of my favorite shoes, but the midsole was so broken that I couldn’t wear them.
So I tried to restore them by making a new midsole with a 3d printer. 
I couldn’t find the midsole used for Rick Owens in Korea easily, so I needed a 3d printer. 
After some trial and error, I succeeded in restoring them. 
The restoration cost was a whopping 5 times the shoe price...! 
But I’m so happy that I can wear my favorite sneakers again! 
Please enjoy the restoration process with asmr.

 

Join my membership !

snippet.title: Restoring Destroyed  1985 Air Jordan 1s and Turning Them to Metallic Purple Customs  | ASMR
snippet.description:
I’m Back!

Here’s a full start to finish ASMR version of a commission for Foxtrot Uniform — Reconstructing an original pair of ’85 Metallic Blues and reconstructing them into the ultra rare Metallic Purple color-way.

Cleaning and conditioning the leather while maintaining the 37 year “patina”.  I replaced old liners, foam, collars, swooshes and tongue. I was unable to reuse the original tongues and collar liners because of wear, as originally planned. These are refitted with the 2021 Jordan Court Purple outsoles that have been dyed in coffee, as well as the original thread, which has been waxed as well. 

Purchase the scans of the deconstructed shoe here! (you can also find my patterns on my website as well)
https://maxhanke.com/shop/p/original-1985-air-jordan-1-scans-6rlgz-rc7ar

Stay updated on Instagram.com/maxio6

localized.title: Restoring Destroyed  1985 Air Jordan 1s and Turning Them to Metallic Purple Customs  | ASMR
localized.description:
I’m Back!

Here’s a full start to finish ASMR version of a commission for Foxtrot Uniform — Reconstructing an original pair of ’85 Metallic Blues and reconstructing them into the ultra rare Metallic Purple color-way.

Cleaning and conditioning the leather while maintaining the 37 year “patina”.  I replaced old liners, foam, collars, swooshes and tongue. I was unable to reuse the original tongues and collar liners because of wear, as originally planned. These are refitted with the 2021 Jordan Court Purple outsoles that have been dyed in coffee, as well as the original thread, which has been waxed as well. 

Purchase the scans of the deconstructed shoe here! (you can also find my patterns on my website as well)
https://maxhanke.com/shop/p/original-1985-air-jordan-1-scans-6rlgz-rc7ar

snippet.title: TRASHED Air Jordan 11 Concord Full Restoration
snippet.description:
TRASHED Air Jordan 11 Concord Full Restoration

In today's episode of Restorations with Vick, he will be working on these beat Concord 11s. Vick used our Essential kit to get the entire shoe cleaned. Starting with the soft brush, he cleaned the entire uppers ensuring he got the shoe nice and bubbly. Moving onto the midsole and outsole, he used the stiff brush to get those deep stains out.  He then moved on to un-yellowing the outsole with salon care 40 to bring it back to its icy self. You can purchase the Essential  kit and other cleaning items online at Reshoevn8r.com

snippet.title: Bringing Dead Js Back To Life: 1985 Air Jordan 1 Restoration
snippet.description:
The 1985 Air Jordan 1 is arguably the best sneaker release in the sneaker game, but how many people can say they still wear them in 2023?!

In today's Customs and Restorations with Vick, Vick pairs up to deconstruct and rebuild a 1985 Jordan 1 Royal to a wearable condition with the help of Flippin Kickz. The full deconstruction process started with removing that outsole/ midsole that literally crumbled in the hands of these two restorers. From there it was time to take this sneaker from its crumbling condition to refurbished. 

This project took days, but hey we would say it was well worth the work! Now we will see Vick rockin' 85 Jordan 1s around the office as his "flex." If you could wear this pair would you?! 

Let us know in the comments if you want to see more of these crazy productions and which 85 Jordan 1 colorway is the GOAT.

snippet.description:
Here at Angelus, we get asked a lot about the difference between our finishers. In this tutorial, @jsm801customs breaks down each one and explains why some may have such a difficult time getting that proper matte look. 
To go a step further, we allowed him to work his magic on a pair of Air Jordan 1 Fearless. He had no problem giving the glossy patent leather a new flat finish. Check it out for yourself!

Thanks for watching and if you have any questions feel free to let us know and don't forget to LIKE and SUBSCRIBE!

snippet.title: How to Custom Paint Air Force 1's Tutorial (Easy In-Depth)
snippet.description:
How to Custom Paint Air Force 1's Tutorial

Hey cuties, in today's video, I explain step by step how I custom paint shoes.  In this case, I'm about to customize Nike Air Force 1's (AF1).  This tutorial is pretty in-depth but it should be easily digestible.  Because they're leather, these steps are a little different than if you paint on a shoe like Vans (which usually consist of canvas material.  Either way, a lot of the steps are the same but the preparation is a little different. 

As you can see, it's a pretty basic design with color blocking.  This shoe still took around 5 or 6 hours total so make sure you are patient with the process to get the best results.

I hope you enjoyed the video!  Leave a comment down below if you have any suggestions of content or how to make videos...new to this so open to learning!

Check out my online sneaker store! DM me on my Instagram for special orders!
https://www.thecustommovement.com/randeeezcustoms
